Chemistry Lab Bench
===================

The reaction-engine pattern and declarative reaction-rule schema in this game
(src/domain/reaction.ts, src/contracts/experiment.ts) are adapted to TypeScript
from the MIT-licensed project:

    chem_lab — https://github.com/nsriram/chem_lab
    Copyright (c) nsriram, MIT License

Only the engine pattern (first-match-wins rule registry resolving an action
against contents into a result) and the rule-schema shape were ported. The engine
was generalised to transform a workspace of named stations — consuming reagents,
producing persistent products, emitting gas, setting a named heat level, and
(in the separation toolkit) routing a station's contents by solubility for
filtration and boiling a solution down by evaporation; that generalisation, the
action/transform vocabulary, the per-step guided flow, the NCERT Class 9
curriculum content, the multi-station mobile-first Canvas presentation, and the
experiment data are original to this project. The original project's
AS-level chemistry content, exam-marking engine, i18n, PDF export, and DOM/emoji
UI are not used here.
